Speaker 2: Um, because it is the HIPAA rules.

Speaker 2: But let's get this taken care of now for you.

Speaker 1: Okay, okay. Thank you.

Speaker 2: So sir, can I just get your full name and date of birth under the prescription?

Speaker 1: James Jones.

Speaker 2: Date of birth 7-29-1966.

Speaker 1: Um.

Speaker 1: I think it might be two.

Speaker 2: Okay, because I see one that is canceled.

Speaker 2: So that being said, I do see your prescription here was written with refills by the doctor on a monthly schedule.

Speaker 1: You're not required to do this.

Speaker 2: This is by no means a subscription. If you wanted to keep access to the remaining refills, I see here—

Speaker 1: You'll no longer receive them monthly.

Speaker 2: Okay, so upon cancellation you would lose access to the remaining refills. Any future prescriptions would require a new and separate health consultation.
